{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
A name probably of Egyptian origin, signifying 'child'. From the root 'moseh' = 'emerge (from the water)'.

===Proper noun===
'''Moses'''

# A name from the [[Old Testament]]. Moses led the slaved Jews out of Egypt. Brother of [[Aaron]] and [[Miriam]] in the Book of [[Exodus]].
#{{given name|male|}} A male [[given name]].

